---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Hugo Esposito-Farese — CS student at 42 Paris, builder, and aspiring founder."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-14">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 mb-3">About</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-8 mb-12">
      <div class="shrink-0">
        <img
          src="/images/hugo_photo_42.jpg"
          alt="Hugo Esposito-Farese"
          class="w-28 h-28 rounded-full bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 object-cover"
          width="112"
          height="112"
        />
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I'm Hugo. I'm a Computer Science student at <a href="https://42.fr" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-zinc-300 underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-white transition-colors">42 Paris</a> — the peer-to-peer coding school with no teachers, no classes, and no traditional curriculum.
        </p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          My long-term goal is to build technology companies. I'm working towards that by building products now, learning what actually matters, and documenting everything in public.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10 max-w-2xl prose">
      <section>
        <h2>Why I build things</h2>
        <p>
          I got into software engineering because I wanted to make things that didn't exist before. Not because I enjoy debugging (I don't) or because I find algorithms beautiful (sometimes).
          Because writing code is one of the few ways a single person can build something and put it in front of millions of people.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm interested in the business side as much as the technical side. Building a product that people pay for is a different problem than building a product that people use, which is a different problem than building something that compiles.
          I want to understand all three layers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Why I document in public</h2>
        <p>
          There's a version of this journey where I spend years getting better at code and graduate with a GitHub full of repositories nobody has used.
          That's not what I want.
        </p>
        <p>
          Publishing forces clarity. If I can't write about what I'm building, I don't really understand it.
          And the builders I find most interesting are the ones who document the actual process — including the things that went wrong.
        </p>
        <p>
          This site is my public build log. Some of these projects will turn into businesses. Some will fail. Both outcomes will be documented here.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What I'm interested in</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>AI-native tools for developers and knowledge workers</li>
          <li>Education technology — specifically, software that teaches by doing</li>
          <li>The early-stage startup process: idea → first user → first dollar</li>
          <li>Systems programming and low-level software (thanks, 42)</li>
          <li>How successful founders thought before they were successful</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What I'm not</h2>
        <p>
          I'm not a senior engineer. I'm not a growth hacker. I don't have a company yet.
          I'm a 20-something student who is learning to build things and trying to do it honestly, in public.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-zinc-800/60">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-medium text-zinc-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Get in touch</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href="https://x.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-sm text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-200 transition-colors border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 hover:border-zinc-700"
        >
          X / Twitter →
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/hugo-esposito-farese"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-sm text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-200 transition-colors border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 hover:border-zinc-700"
        >
          GitHub →
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://fr.linkedin.com/in/hugo-esposito-farese-530045407"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-sm text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-200 transition-colors border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 hover:border-zinc-700"
        >
          LinkedIn →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
